
Write a complete Java program in a class named EggStop that generates the following output. Use static methods to show structure and eliminate redundancy in your solution.

  ______
 /      \
/        \
\        /
 \______/

  ______
 /      \
/        \
\        /
 \______/
+--------+

  ______
 /      \
/        \
|  STOP  |
\        /
 \______/
+--------+

SOLUTION:
public class  EggStop {

    public static void main(String[] args){

        top1();
        bottom1();
        System.out.println();

        top1();
        bottom1();
        middle1();

        System.out.println();

        top1();
        stop();
        bottom1();
        middle1();


    }

    public static void top1(){

        System.out.println("  ______      ");
        System.out.println(" /      \\    ");
        System.out.println("/        \\ ");

    }

    public static void bottom1(){

        System.out.println("\\        /");
        System.out.println(" \\______/ ");



    }

    public static void middle1(){

        System.out.println("+--------+");

    }

    public static void stop(){

        System.out.println("|  STOP  |");


    }


}
